nodes.directive:
Present architecture analysis/design to user for approval (quality gate G1/G3/G4).

Present a structured summary to the user:

{{#if functional_requirements}}
**For Scenario A (new project):**
- Requirements summary: {{functional_requirements}}, {{non_functional_requirements}}
- Domain model: {{bounded_contexts}}, {{context_map_mermaid}}
- System context: {{context_diagram_mermaid}}
- Containers and technology choices: {{containers}}, {{container_diagram_mermaid}}
- Component designs: {{component_designs}}
{{/if}}

{{#if languages}}
**For Scenario B (existing project):**
- Scan summary: {{languages}}, {{frameworks}}
- Architecture as-is: {{containers}}, {{container_diagram_mermaid}}
- Bounded contexts: {{bounded_contexts}}, {{context_map_mermaid}}
- Gaps found: {{gaps}}
- Proposed improvements: {{improvements}}
- Target architecture: {{target_container_diagram_mermaid}}
{{/if}}

Ask user: "Do you approve this scope and direction? Or do you have feedback?"

Fix architecture issues found by subagent review.

Review findings (all mandatory to fix — no severity tiers):
- {{subagent-review.blocking_issues}}
- {{subagent-review.major_issues}}

Fix iteration: {{fix_iteration_count}} of {{max_fix_iterations}}

1. Address EVERY issue — all are mandatory, none optional
2. Update affected diagrams and artifacts
3. Document what was changed and why

CRITICAL: Actually fix the architecture — update diagrams, change technology choices, restructure components. Do not just acknowledge issues.

Use: {{architecture_principles}}, {{common_architecture_mistakes}}

Compile all artifacts into architecture documentation package (methodology stage C4).

Assemble using {{planning_standards}} directory structure:

1. Create docs/architecture/ directory
2. Create INDEX.md with navigation links
3. Create overview.md — Architecture Overview (arc42 sections 1-4, 8, 10) consolidating all work
4. Create context-diagram.md with C4 Level 1: {{context_diagram_mermaid}}
5. Create container-diagram.md with C4 Level 2: {{container_diagram_mermaid}}
6. Create component-{name}.md for each component design: {{component_designs}}
7. Create bounded-context-map.md: {{context_map_mermaid}}, {{bounded_contexts}}
8. Create quality-attributes.md: {{quality-attributes.quality_scenarios}}
9. Create risks-and-debt.md: {{#if gaps}}{{gaps}}, {{tech_debt}} (Scenario B){{else}}anticipated risks (Scenario A){{/if}}
10. Create glossary.md: {{glossary}}
11. Create adr/NNNN-title.md for each ADR: {{create-adrs.adrs}}
12. For library/package projects: create api-surface.md with public API inventory (exports, signatures, stability guarantees, deprecation status)
13. Add YAML front matter to every file
14. Verify all Mermaid diagrams render
15. Verify all cross-references between documents

**VALIDATION CHECKS:**
1. All applicable artifact types present (or N/A justified)
2. INDEX.md complete with links
3. YAML front matter on every file
4. No TODO/placeholder sections
5. All Mermaid diagrams render
6. Cross-references valid
7. For library projects: api-surface.md present

Return issues_count.
